HEADWORD: Cuir bouilli
<hw>Cuir" bou`illi"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>In
decorative art, boiled leather, fitted by the process to receive
impressed patterns, like those produced by chasing metal, and to retain
the impression permanently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuish</ent>⟦br⟧
